 fine for most people. Seriously though, you probably won't need an Intuos if you're not doing art full-time. <p><div align=right><embed src="http://homepage.mac.com/tumult/ultraflag.swf" width=180 height=120></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uaetheros.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aetheros</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fresh Meat</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/17/01 12:40:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wacom Graphire tablets?</span><hr size=1> It's simply the best choice for a non professional user <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ufutura2001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Futura2001</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/17/01 3:23:44 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.att.net/~polysin/Futura_Copy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wacom Graphire tablets?</span><hr size=1> No, an intuos is the best choice, you can get a 6x8 intuos of of ebay for $50 from businesses and studios that need to get rid of them, that is 30 less than a Graphire and graphire tablets are imprecise crap. <p>I looked to the future and I looked to the past, One in the middle and one in last.
One is what I've been and one is what I'll become, I looked at time and it made my soul numb.
If you mess with me you'll get one through the eye and one through lip, and all the while coming from the hip.             ~Futura2001~
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/urist385.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rist385</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/17/01 5:10:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wacom Graphire tablets?</span><hr size=1> I would steal an Intous from an old lady who has one. Hahaha! Take that hag!<br>
