</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ushousetsu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shousetsu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.newelysium.com/forum/psicon.gif width=13 height=13 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/17/01 5:19:59 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.newelysium.com/forum/photo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wacom Graphire tablets?</span><hr size=1> wacom doesnt even suggest that size for illustrators. Why? Just to do something as little as to change layers you will have to move your hand to the other side of a gigantic tablet, then to make a simple line you would have to do the same. It gets old fast and is anything but practical.<br>
<br>
I would rather pay $10 for a 4x5 Intous than $5 for a 12x12 <p><a href="http://www.newelysium.com"><img src="http://www.newelysium.com/banners/newelysium4.gif" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ufutura2001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Futura2001</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/17/01 6:59:51 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.att.net/~polysin/Futura_Copy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wacom Graphire tablets?</span><hr size=1> Oh, but I would rather pay $20 for a 6x8 than $5 for a 4x5, a 4x5 feels like drawing on a baseball card and a 6x8 feels about right.  I don't care about the zoom function on a 4x5, it still feels like drawing on a baseball card. <p>I looked to the future and I looked to the past, One in the middle and one in last.
